    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "But is it actually \"mitigatable\"? It seems like you're framing the benefits as these huge, structural advantages like innovation and pension support, while the downsides just sound like temporary problems that can be fixed with enough money or policy. Isn't there a real risk that the economic damage to certain communities is just a fundamental reality of high immigration levels?",
